HEADWORD: Smaragdite
<hw>Sma*rag"dite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>smaragdite</ets>; -- so called from its emerald-green color. See
<er>Smaragd</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A green foliated kind of
amphibole, observed in eclogite and some varietis of gabbro.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

